<br>
Also, I am curious about the Sword of the Morning and the affect DEX has on the Tishan's Clash proc rate. Is there a magic DEX number to get more procs? My DEX is currently 83 and I wonder if that would matter.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts?<br>
<br>
-Ylem<br>
53 Paladin <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uylem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylem</A> at: 5/10/01 6:35:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umemnenthmoondust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Memnenth Moondust</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 6:45:35 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://cyric.manleyweb.com/images/memmy.jpg height=350 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoM: Is it the best if you don't have an epic?</span><hr size=1> depends on if youre main tank... and if youre on a raid I hope youre not ;), on a raid youll wanna be doing most damage you can, so pick up and Arb sword, BoF or something to that effect... main tank in group use the SoM/SBS combo <p><font size=6 color=darkred>Memnenth</font>
<br>
<font size=5 color=blue>55th Level Knight of Mithaniel Marr</font>
<br>
<font size=4 color=darkgreen>Prexus Server</font>
<br>
<a href="http://www.fallenalliance.com"><i>Fallen Alliance</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 6:46:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoM: Is it the best if you don't have an epic?</span><hr size=1> SoM is a very nice 1HS weapon. But there are now tons of weapons way more powerful than it.<br>
If you are looking for straight damage dealing, than pretty much all of the uber and even old world uber 2handers ( ORB, Arbitors, etc..)will outdamage your SoM. Of course you won't have the added ac + stats + bash of the shield.<br>
Personally, I have been using 2HS pretty much exclusively since about 24th level. I have toyed around with different 1HS and 1HB combo's, of course nothing in the SoM realm, but haven't been satisfied with it. If you want an uber upgrade to the SoM for 1HS, I would suggest trying for a darkmetal falchion in second floor of hate. They aren't a common drop, but they aren't super super rare. 23/29 +7wis/int is pretty uber =)<br>
It depends on what  you are looking for I suppose. And what sort of a force you can get together to take down the baddies for the more uber stuff. Alot of the newer velious weapons from DN and WW and velks lab are going to destroy the SoM.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the SoM is definitely a fine weapon. but you certainly have some upgrade paths. As far as dex is concerned I think that the safehouse rogues have done some pretty extensive research on dex level vs procs. Above 75% is a definite must. going from 75-100 gives you a pretty reasonable upgrade in chance to proc. anything after 100 isn't really going to be a huge improvement. Unless you can get up to 200+. I may be off on those numbers but I'm pretty sure those are the cutoffs. <br>
Hope that helps a bit.<br>
<br>
<br>
Biz.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uderringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Derringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 6:52:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoM: Is it the best if you don't have an epic?</span><hr size=1> I must agree with what is being said here.  While the SoM is a fine weapon, you should consider an upgrade path which takes you to a good 2hander by your mid 50s.  I would suggest trying to get a group into Dragon Necropolis at some point to feast on some of the finest weapons to be found anywhere in EQ.  Since I attained my Forged Velium Claidhmore at about level 56 there, i have never used anything but SoSh for a proc and a 1-hander when I was in my Healing Gear.  I don't even lose it when I need resists, as the Damage per Minute of it at 30-35 smokes almost everything else by a long shot, coming up only marginally short of our Epic. <p>Derringer Labyrinth
60 Crusader of Pak'Cafan
Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrueheart78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trueheart78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 6:57:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoM: Is it the best if you don't have an epic?</span><hr size=1> I've yet to play with an ORB, But I have used a SoM, Sprinkler, ACG, and Rod of lamentation. and of these that I have toyed with, the RoL clearly outshines the rest in damage, taunt, and a fun proc to boot (procs our lvl 52 stun, Force)<br>
<br>
For quite awhile I had wanted to trade my RoL for a SoM until Felen I think it was(maybe Mithas?) let me borrow his. At the time, it outshone my ACG due to proc and speed... and bash.  But since I've gotten a RoL I can honestly say that neither the ACG nor SOM can compare in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Sure, it's not an Epic weapon, a gfg or such would probably tear it up... but it's Soooooooooo Fun! It's proc just makes me smile(so long as it's not pushing mobs off from rooftops) and that's what the game is all about.<br>
<br>
Now, if only I could get a rod of mourning...<br>
