Claim Trueheart, 21 Monk - </FONT><FONT COLOR="blue">Bristlebane</FONT></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugreymoormistloch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greymoor Mistloch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 7:31:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SoM: Is it the best if you don't have an epic?</span><hr size=1> Sword of the Morning gets OWNED by the Massive Dragonclaw Shard and the Darkmetal Falchion. Until you have one of those, please do yourself a favor and get a nice 2 hander. I am almost NEVER the main tank in exp groups and definitely not on raids. As others here have stated, if you are main tank, AC of the shield is good. If you aren't, you MUST concentrate on dealing damage. <br>
<br>
I know you'll probably say, &quot;but Paladins aren't good damage dealers and never will be so we should always be utilizing the greater AC of a shield&quot;. Well, I say that it's time to turn that myth araound. A Paladin with a GFG or a Velium weapon actually does decent damage. Even a Paladin with an ACG or an ORB will do more damage than the SotM. <br>
<br>
The Sword of the Morning is a nice weapon, don't get me wrong. However, I would rather spend my 15-20K on a GFG plus some armor, or a Velium weapon than buy a SotM. I think Paladins need to get into the mind set that they CAN be decent damage dealers with the right equipment.  <p>Greymoor Mistloch<br>
Cavalier of Tunare<br>
Society of Shadows<br>Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugolorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 7:48:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my 2 cents</span><hr size=1>   Right now i have a rod of mourning and a massive dragon claw shard, while i do a lot more dmg with rod of mourning, i can use a 40 ac fearsome shield with the shard, which is a big incentive.  Because of that incentive i use the massive dragon claw shard and fearsome shield, but to those who don't have the shield and sword, i recommend a 2 hander, i rarely find situations where i'm main tank, and if i am, you still want to go 2 hander because you need to taunt to be main tank, and hitting for 20's isn't gonna do it.  I recommend at lvl 40's-50's, use a good 2hander, rod of lammy, grinder, arbitor, etc...<br>
           Golorn Evilslayer<br>
