</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quixotimomniscience>Quixotim Omniscience</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/01 3:14:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my 2 cents</span><hr size=1> Actually, I think one of the more probable weapons to obtain for a mid 50s paladin looking for a good one-hander is the Sword of Blessings.  19/27 is a sweet ratio for a drop that is not infrequent.  It's in Velks and drops off of a lvl 58 MoB.  1 group of 55+ can take him out.  Whereas I too go for the greater dam 2h weapons during raids, keeping up all weapons skills is something I firmly believe in.  Moreover, when one is clearly the main tank (often the case for me in KC) then 1h with a shield is great. <p>Quixotim Omniscience<BR>
